{"title_page": "Lansana Sagna", "text_new": "{{short description|Senegalese footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Lansana Sagna\n| image          =\n| fullname       = Lansana Sagna\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1994|02|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Dakar]], Senegal<ref name=ft/>\n| height         = 1.86 m\n| currentclub    = [[US Feurs]]\n| clubnumber     = \n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Centre back]]<ref name=fb/>\n| youthyears1    = 2012\u20132013\n| youthclubs1    = [[FC Porto|Porto]]<ref name=ft/>\n| years1         = 2013      | clubs1 = RC Dakar             | caps1 =   | goals1 = \n| years2         = 2014\u20132015 | clubs2 = [[\u00dajpest FC|\u00dajpest]] | caps2 = 1 | goals2 = 0\n| years3         = 2015\u20132018 | clubs3 = [[AS Douanes (Senegal)|AS Douanes]] | caps3 =  | goals3 = \n| years4         = 2018\u20132019 | clubs4 = [[UMS Mont\u00e9limar|Mont\u00e9limar]] | caps4 =  | goals4 = \n| years5         = 2019\u2013     | clubs5 = [[US Feurs]] | caps5 =  | goals5 = \n| pcupdate       = 00:47, 18 October 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Lansana Sagna''' (born 17 February 1994) is a Senegalese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defender (association football)|centre back]] for [[\u00dajpest FC]].\n\n==Career==\nHaving played for [[FC Porto]]'s U19-squad from 2012 to 2013, Sagna moved back to Senegal and played for Racing Club de Dakar. In January 2014, he signed with [[\u00dajpest FC]] from Hungary together with his friend and teammate [[Elhadji Badiane Sidibe]].<ref name=ft>[http://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo_nb_i/ujpest-a-19-eves-sagna-es-sidibe-alairt-a-lila-feherekhez-2311423 \u00dajpest: a 19 \u00e9ves Sagna \u00e9s Sidibe al\u00e1\u00edrt a lila-feh\u00e9rekhez], nemzetisport.hu, 29 January 2014</ref> \n\nOn 5 December 2018, Sagna joined French club [[UMS Mont\u00e9limar]].<ref name=fb>[http://umsfoot-montelimar.fr/2018/12/05/deux-puis-trois-renforts-a-lums/ DEUX PUIS TROIS RENFORTS A L\u2019UMS], umsfoot-montelimar.fr, 5 December 2018</ref> He was released by the club in June 2019 and a few weeks later joined [[US Feurs]].<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=360217697969373&id=112015252789620&substory_index=0 US Feurs - [ Mercato ] Nouvelle recrue de choc avec...], facebook.com, 25 July 2019</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{FootballDatabase.eu|227914}}\n* [http://www.mlsz.hu/player/?itemId=621891 MLSZ] {{in lang|hu}}\n* [http://hlsz.hu/index.php?tid=7&Jatekos=hPLf_149f04c HLSZ] {{in lang|hu}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sagna, Lansana}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Senegalese footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:\u00dajpest FC players]]\n[[Category:AS Douanes (Senegal) players]]\n[[Category:UMS Mont\u00e9limar players]]\n[[Category:US Feurs players]]\n[[Category:Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I players]]\n[[Category:Senegalese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Senegalese expatriate sportspeople in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Hungary]]\n[[Category:Senegalese expatriate sportspeople in Hungary]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in France]]\n[[Category:Senegalese expatriate sportspeople in France]]\n{{Senegal-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Senegalese footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Lansana Sagna\n| image          =\n| fullname       = Lansana Sagna\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1994|02|17|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Dakar]], Senegal<ref name=ft/>\n| height         = {{height|m=1.86|precision=0}}\n| currentclub    = [[US Feurs]]\n| clubnumber     = \n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Centre back]]<ref name=fb/>\n| youthyears1    = 2012\u20132013\n| youthclubs1    = [[FC Porto]]<ref name=ft/>\n| years1         = 2013      | clubs1 = RC Dakar             | caps1 =   | goals1 = \n| years2         = 2014\u20132015 | clubs2 = [[\u00dajpest FC|\u00dajpest]] | caps2 = 1 | goals2 = 0\n| years3         = 2015\u20132018 | clubs3 = [[AS Douanes (Senegal)|AS Douanes]] | caps3 =  | goals3 = \n| years4         = 2018\u20132019 | clubs4 = [[UMS Mont\u00e9limar|Mont\u00e9limar]] | caps4 =  | goals4 = \n| years5         = 2019\u2013     | clubs5 = [[US Feurs]] | caps5 =  | goals5 = \n| pcupdate       = 00:47, 18 October 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Lansana Sagna''' (born 17 February 1994) is a Senegalese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[\u00dajpest FC]].\n\n==Career==\nHaving played for [[FC Portos]]' U19-squad from 2012 to 2013, Sagna moved back to Senegal and played for Racing Club de Dakar. In January 2014, he signed with [[\u00dajpest FC]] from Hungary together with his friend and teammate [[Elhadji Badiane Sidibe]].<ref name=ft>[http://www.nemzetisport.hu/labdarugo_nb_i/ujpest-a-19-eves-sagna-es-sidibe-alairt-a-lila-feherekhez-2311423 \u00dajpest: a 19 \u00e9ves Sagna \u00e9s Sidibe al\u00e1\u00edrt a lila-feh\u00e9rekhez], nemzetisport.hu, 29 January 2014</ref> \n\nOn 5 December 2018, Sagna joined French club [[UMS Mont\u00e9limar]].<ref name=fb>[http://umsfoot-montelimar.fr/2018/12/05/deux-puis-trois-renforts-a-lums/ DEUX PUIS TROIS RENFORTS A L\u2019UMS], umsfoot-montelimar.fr, 5 December 2018</ref> He was released by the club in June 2019 and a few weeks later joined [[US Feurs]].<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=360217697969373&id=112015252789620&substory_index=0 US Feurs - [ Mercato ] Nouvelle recrue de choc avec...], facebook.com, 25 July 2019</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.mlsz.hu/player/?itemId=621891 MLSZ] {{in lang|hu}}\n*[http://hlsz.hu/index.php?tid=7&Jatekos=hPLf_149f04c HLSZ] {{in lang|hu}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2014}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sagna, Lansana}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n